    "After a monograph on Florentine culture, <em>L'Architettura dell'Umanesimo</em>, 1969, the second of his broad Marxist salvos, <em>Progetto e Utopia</em>, appeared in 1973, a historical assessment of architecture's relationship with capitalist development since the eighteenth century.": [],
    "Tafuri's innovative book subjects continued with <em>La citt\u00e0 americana</em> and <em>Via Giulia</em> (a book of a Roman street) in 1973, the latter with <a href=\"/salernol\">Luigi Salerno</a> and <a href=\"/spezzaferrol\">Luigi Spezzaferro</a>, and regularly contributed to the American journal <em>Oppositions</em> as well as the European journals <em>Casabella</em>, <em>Domus</em>, and <em>L'Architecture d'aujourd'hui</em>.": [
