    "<em>Venezia e il rinascimento</em> appeared in 1985 followed by a broad and polemical assessment of Italy's architectural history since the end of World War Two, <em>Storia dell'architettura italiana, 1944-85</em>, 1986, in which he castigated those architects who had ensured a the trajectory from post-war ineffectuality to postmodern frivolity, particularly Carlo Aymonino and Carlo Scarpa.": [],
