    "As the head of the so-called Venice School of architectural history, he exerted a substantial influence over generations of architects, historians and theorists in Italy, Europe and North America.": [],
    "Tafuri's <em>Teorie e storia dell'architettura</em>, stands as \"a pointed assessment of historical knowledge in architecture that positioned the architectural historian as an agent of institutional and political change\" (Leach).": [
