    "<em>Progetto e Utopia</em>, was a more pointed Marxist historical assessment of architecture's relationship with capitalist development since the eighteenth century.": [],
    "As a theorist, he saw capitalist production and consumption eroding values, not stabilizing them, and hence the modern era was not able to create a context of belief in which architecture could flower.": [],
    "Tafuri insisted there was no difference between criticism and history--that the tools and tasks (relative to contemporary architectural culture) remained constant as distance from the subject moved in time.": [
